server.longdesc: Splash Client for connecting Odoo Erp Systems

fields.name: Activity State
fields.desc:
Status based on activities
Overdue: Due date is already passed
Today: Activity date is today
Planned: Future activities.

fields.name: Barcode
fields.desc: Use a barcode to identify this contact from the Point of Sale.

fields.name: Total Receivable
fields.desc: Total amount this customer owes you.

fields.name: Is a Customer
fields.desc: Check this box if this contact is a customer. It can be selected in sales orders.

fields.name: Total Payable
fields.desc: Total amount you have to pay to this vendor.

fields.name: Employee
fields.desc: Check this box if this contact is an Employee.

fields.name: Has Unreconciled Entries
fields.desc: The partner has at least one unreconciled debit and credit since last time the invoices & payments matching was performed.

fields.name: Invoice
fields.desc: Selecting the "Warning" option will notify user with the message, Selecting "Blocking Message" will throw an exception with the message and block the flow. The Message has to be written in the next field.

fields.name: Blacklist
fields.desc: If the email address is on the blacklist, the contact won't receive mass mailing anymore, from any list

fields.name: Is a Company
fields.desc: Check if the contact is a company, otherwise it is a person

fields.name: Language
fields.desc: All the emails and documents sent to this contact will be translated in this language.

fields.name: Latest Invoices & Payments Matching Date
fields.desc: Last time the invoices & payments matching was performed for this partner. It is set either if there's not at least an unreconciled debit and an unreconciled credit or if you click the "Done" button.

fields.name: Bounce
fields.desc: Counter of the number of bounced emails for this contact

fields.name: Message Delivery error
fields.desc: If checked, some messages have a delivery error.

fields.name: Number of error
fields.desc: Number of messages with delivery error

fields.name: Action Needed
fields.desc: If checked, new messages require your attention.

fields.name: Number of Actions
fields.desc: Number of messages which requires an action

fields.name: Unread Messages
fields.desc: If checked new messages require your attention.

fields.name: Share Partner
fields.desc: Either customer (not a user), either shared user. Indicated the current partner is a customer without access or with a limited access created for sharing data.

fields.name: Stock Picking
fields.desc: Selecting the "Warning" option will notify user with the message, Selecting "Blocking Message" will throw an exception with the message and block the flow. The Message has to be written in the next field.

fields.name: Purchase Order
fields.desc: Selecting the "Warning" option will notify user with the message, Selecting "Blocking Message" will throw an exception with the message and block the flow. The Message has to be written in the next field.

fields.name: Sales Warnings
fields.desc: Selecting the "Warning" option will notify user with the message, Selecting "Blocking Message" will throw an exception with the message and block the flow. The Message has to be written in the next field.

fields.name: Is a Vendor
fields.desc: Check this box if this contact is a vendor. It can be selected in purchase orders.

fields.name: Degree of trust you have in this debtor
fields.desc: Degree of trust you have in this debtor
fields.itemprop: Degree of trust you have in this debtor

fields.name: Address Type
fields.desc: Used by Sales and Purchase Apps to select the relevant address depending on the context.

fields.name: Timezone
fields.desc: The partner's timezone, used to output proper date and time values inside printed reports. It is important to set a value for this field. You should use the same timezone that is otherwise used to pick and render date and time values: your computer's timezone.

fields.name: Tax ID
fields.desc: The Tax Identification Number. Complete it if the contact is subjected to government taxes. Used in some legal statements.

fields.name: Image
fields.desc: This field holds the image used as avatar for this contact, limited to 1024x1024px

fields.name: Activity State
fields.desc:
Status based on activities
Overdue: Due date is already passed
Today: Activity date is today
Planned: Future activities.

fields.name: Commitment Date
fields.desc: This is the delivery date promised to the customer. If set, the delivery order will be scheduled based on this date rather than product lead times.

fields.name: Confirmation Date
fields.desc: Date on which the sales order is confirmed.

fields.name: Creation Date
fields.desc: Date on which sales order is created.

fields.name: Currency Rate
fields.desc: The rate of the currency to the currency of rate 1 applicable at the date of the order

fields.name: Effective Date
fields.desc: Completion date of the first delivery order.

fields.name: Expected Date
fields.desc: Delivery date you can promise to the customer, computed from product lead times and from the shipping policy of the order.

fields.name: Message Delivery error
fields.desc: If checked, some messages have a delivery error.

fields.name: Number of error
fields.desc: Number of messages with delivery error

fields.name: Action Needed
fields.desc: If checked, new messages require your attention.

fields.name: Number of Actions
fields.desc: Number of messages which requires an action

fields.name: Unread Messages
fields.desc: If checked new messages require your attention.

fields.name: Source Document
fields.desc: Reference of the document that generated this sales order request.

fields.name: Shipping Policy
fields.desc: If you deliver all products at once, the delivery order will be scheduled based on the greatest product lead time. Otherwise, it will be based on the shortest.

fields.name: Payment Ref.
fields.desc: The payment communication of this sale order.

fields.name: Online Payment
fields.desc: Request an online payment to the customer in order to confirm orders automatically.

fields.name: Online Signature
fields.desc: Request a online signature to the customer in order to confirm orders automatically.

fields.name: Signed by
fields.desc: Name of the person that signed the SO.

fields.name: Validity
fields.desc: Validity date of the quotation, after this date, the customer won't be able to validate the quotation online.

fields.name: Tax amount by group
fields.desc: type: [(name, amount, base, formated amount, formated base)]

fields.desc: If unchecked, it will allow you to hide the product without removing it.

fields.name: Activity State
fields.desc:
Status based on activities
Overdue: Due date is already passed
Today: Activity date is today
Planned: Future activities.

fields.name: Barcode
fields.desc: International Article Number used for product identification.

fields.name: Re-Invoice Policy
fields.desc: Expenses and vendor bills can be re-invoiced to a customer.With this option, a validated expense can be re-invoice to a customer at its cost or sales price.

fields.name: Incoming
fields.desc:
Quantity of planned incoming products.
In a context with a single Stock Location, this includes goods arriving to this Location, or any of its children.
In a context with a single Warehouse, this includes goods arriving to the Stock Location of this Warehouse, or any of its children.
Otherwise, this includes goods arriving to any Stock Location with 'internal' type.

fields.name: Inventory Availability

item-1.value: Show inventory on website and prevent sales if not enough stock

item-2.value: Show inventory below a threshold and prevent sales if not enough stock

fields.desc: Adds an inventory availability status on the web product page.

fields.name: Invoicing Policy
fields.desc:
Ordered Quantity: Invoice quantities ordered by the customer.
Delivered Quantity: Invoice quantities delivered to the customer.

fields.name: Message Delivery error
fields.desc: If checked, some messages have a delivery error.

fields.name: Number of error
fields.desc: Number of messages with delivery error

fields.name: Action Needed
fields.desc: If checked, new messages require your attention.

fields.name: Number of Actions
fields.desc: Number of messages which requires an action

fields.name: Unread Messages
fields.desc: If checked new messages require your attention.

fields.name: Outgoing
fields.desc:
Quantity of planned outgoing products.
In a context with a single Stock Location, this includes goods leaving this Location, or any of its children.
In a context with a single Warehouse, this includes goods leaving the Stock Location of this Warehouse, or any of its children.
Otherwise, this includes goods leaving any Stock Location with 'internal' type.

fields.name: Costing Method
fields.desc:
Standard Price: The products are valued at their standard cost defined on the product.
        Average Cost (AVCO): The products are valued at weighted average cost.
        First In First Out (FIFO): The products are valued supposing those that enter the company first will also leave it first.

fields.name: Inventory Valuation
fields.desc:
Manual: The accounting entries to value the inventory are not posted automatically.
        Automated: An accounting entry is automatically created to value the inventory when a product enters or leaves the company.

fields.name: Control Policy
fields.desc:
On ordered quantities: Control bills based on ordered quantities.
On received quantities: Control bills based on received quantities.

fields.name: Quantity On Hand
fields.desc:
Current quantity of products.
In a context with a single Stock Location, this includes goods stored at this Location, or any of its children.
In a context with a single Warehouse, this includes goods stored in the Stock Location of this Warehouse, or any of its children.
stored in the Stock Location of the Warehouse of this Shop, or any of its children.
Otherwise, this includes goods stored in any Stock Location with 'internal' type.

fields.name: Customer Lead Time
fields.desc: Delivery lead time, in days. It's the number of days, promised to the customer, between the confirmation of the sales order and the delivery.

fields.name: Sequence
fields.desc: Gives the sequence order when displaying a product list

fields.name: Track Service
fields.desc:
Manually set quantities on order: Invoice based on the manually entered quantity, without creating an analytic account.
Timesheets on contract: Invoice based on the tracked hours on the related timesheet.
Create a task and track hours: Create a task on the sales order validation and track the work hours.

fields.name: Product Type
fields.desc:
A storable product is a product for which you manage stock. The Inventory app has to be installed.
A consumable product is a product for which stock is not managed.
A service is a non-material product you provide.

fields.name: Forecast Quantity
fields.desc:
Forecast quantity (computed as Quantity On Hand - Outgoing + Incoming)
In a context with a single Stock Location, this includes goods stored in this location, or any of its children.
In a context with a single Warehouse, this includes goods stored in the Stock Location of this Warehouse, or any of its children.
Otherwise, this includes goods stored in any Stock Location with 'internal' type.

fields.name: Website Sequence
fields.desc: Determine the display order in the Website E-commerce

fields.name: Website URL
fields.desc: The full URL to access the document through the website.

fields.name: Weight
fields.desc: Weight of the product, packaging not included. The unit of measure can be changed in the general settings

fields.name: Weight unit of measure label
fields.desc: Weight unit of measure label [French / Français]

fields.name: Base Price (tax excl.)
fields.desc: Base Price for this Product & Variants.

fields.name: Activity State
fields.desc:
Status based on activities
Overdue: Due date is already passed
Today: Activity date is today
Planned: Future activities.

fields.name: Total in Company Currency
fields.desc: Total amount in the currency of the company, negative for credit notes.

fields.name: Total in Invoice Currency
fields.desc: Total amount in the currency of the invoice, negative for credit notes.

fields.name: Accounting Date
fields.desc: Keep empty to use the invoice date.

fields.name: Due Date
fields.desc: If you use payment terms, the due date will be computed automatically at the generation of accounting entries. The Payment terms may compute several due dates, for example 50% now and 50% in one month, but if you want to force a due date, make sure that the payment term is not set on the invoice. If you keep the Payment terms and the due date empty, it means direct payment.

fields.name: Message Delivery error
fields.desc: If checked, some messages have a delivery error.

fields.name: Number of error
fields.desc: Number of messages with delivery error

fields.name: Action Needed
fields.desc: If checked, new messages require your attention.

fields.name: Number of Actions
fields.desc: Number of messages which requires an action

fields.name: Reference/Description
fields.desc: The name that will be used on account move lines

fields.name: Source Document
fields.desc: Reference of the document that produced this invoice.

fields.name: Paid/Reconciled
fields.desc: It indicates that the invoice has been paid and the journal entry of the invoice has been reconciled with one or several journal entries of payment.

fields.name: Payment Ref.
fields.desc: The payment communication that will be automatically populated once the invoice validation. You can also write a free communication.

fields.name: Amount Due in Company Currency
fields.desc: Remaining amount due in the currency of the company.

fields.name: Amount Due in Invoice Currency
fields.desc: Remaining amount due in the currency of the invoice.

fields.name: Sent
fields.desc: It indicates that the invoice has been sent.

fields.name: Tax amount by group
fields.desc: type: [(name, amount, base, formated amount, formated base)]
